President Obama released a statement expressing his concern and support for Richard Holbrooke, a prominent figure in American foreign policy. Holbrooke is a crucial member of Obama's Afghanistan and Pakistan team and has earned the admiration of the American people and people worldwide. The President assured Holbrooke's wife, Kati, that he and Michelle are praying for Richard's recovery. Secretary Clinton, Admiral Mullen, Tom Donilon, and other members of the team have been by Holbrooke's side at the George Washington hospital. The President asked for continued prayers and offered support to Holbrooke's family during this challenging time.